Compute the ending point of the provided line segment along the 'x' axis.



```kcl
segEndX(tag: [TagIdentifier](/docs/kcl/types#TagIdentifier)): [number](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-number)
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| [`tag`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-tag) | [`TagIdentifier`](/docs/kcl/types#TagIdentifier) | The line segment being queried by its tag | Yes |

### Returns

[`number`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-number)


### Examples

```kcl
exampleSketch = startSketchOn(XZ)
  |> startProfile(at = [0, 0])
  |> line(end = [20, 0], tag = $thing)
  |> line(end = [0, 5])
  |> line(end = [segEndX(thing), 0])
  |> line(end = [-20, 10])
  |> close()

example = extrude(exampleSketch, length = 5)
```
